jyzer.items.factories
Class AttributeFactory

java.lang.Object
  jyzer.items.factories.AttributeFactory

public class AttributeFactory
extends java.lang.Object

A singleton factory to create instances of attributes. Every object that has any attributes should delegate the request here to create an attribute. To create them on your own is permitted, but use them at your own risk!

Version:
1.0, 2005 oct 17
Author:
Legendi Richard Oliver

                            throws java.io.IOException,

A static method to create an attribute from the given DataInput.

Returns:
the created AttributeInfo.
Throws:
java.io.IOException - if an I/O error occurs.
CorruptedClassfileException - when the required attribute lenght is not equal to the read length.
